sentences: Mauro Scocco (born 11 September 1962) is a Swedish pop artist of Italian descent.
Scocco was the singer for the pop group Ratata (1980–83) transformed into a duo with Johan Ekelund (1983–89).

In 2014, he cooperated with Plura Jonsson releasing a joint album as Mauro & Plura.
Scocco formed the pop group Ratata in 1980 along with a few classmates while he was still in school.
The first single was "För varje dag" ("For each day") released on the debut album Ratata in 1981.

In 1991, Scocco released an album with instrumental piano music, Det Sjungande Trädet ("The singing tree"), with inspiration from Erik Satie and expressionistic art.
In the spring of 2004, Scocco was a disc jockey in the talkshow Sen kväll med Luuk on TV4, in line with the dry, ironic humour of the show.

Mauro Scocco was also a lead singer of the four-piece band Swedish band Ratata formed in 1980 made up of Scocco and Heinz Liljedahl, Anders Skog, Johan Kling.
Their debut single was "För varje dag" in 1981 followed by "Ögon av is".
Both appeared in their self-titled 1982 debut album Ratata.
